            * If a course focused around intrinsic motivation runs in parallel with another course that has extrinsic rewards and surveillance, then the latter course seems to block the more open ended activities in the former.  
                * Tasks with extrinsic motivators tend to get the priority. 
                * Yet the tasks with a more intrinsic focus are those which the students want to elaborate on later after the course was finished. 
  
  }
